  title: Can you give an example of a situation where an assertion might be used?
  text: 'An assertion might be used to verify that an input parameter to a method
    is not null when null is NOT a valid argument for that method. For example, Debug.Assert(param
    != null); ensures that param is not null during development, helping catch bugs
    early.

    This is different from doing a null check when using null as a parameter
    might be a valid use case.'
